Mpumalanga’s head of Cogta Samukelo Ngubane appeared in the Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court today, June 6. The provincial directorate for priority crime investigation (Hawks) spokesperson, Captain Dineo Sekgotodi, said Ngubane was arrested for the contravention of the Public finance management act, Section 86(1), with sections 36, 38, 39, 40, 41, 77 and 81 regarding a PPE contract that was awarded. He was released on R10 000 bail and is next set to appear in the Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court on July 28.